@10055  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Elvenhair send a messenger: he brought his Ruathlek lexicon from Candlekeep and is waiting in his house in Beregost, ready to help Brandock with the translation. Brandock is eager to go there as soon as possible.~
@10056  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Apparently, the De Simplex Magicae had some sort of safety feature implemented which transformed the destroyed pages back into a magic book when Elvenhair and Brandock attempted to conserve the remaining pages. Now it has an introduction in a rune language saying: 
"So, whoever of you fools damaged the book, you found out that a preservation spell makes the book physically whole again. I expect you to make detailed notes about the process, as I want to expand this spell as a way of preserving magical books in whole. So far it only restores the blank pages. Let it be a lesson to you to take better care of magic books in the future. I expect you to fill the pages with spells again - they should continue to benefit from the magic of the book and should be effective accordingly without cost. But let me tell you: this will be a long road for you, because wih your current experience you don't even need to try. And before you do anything, make sure you seek Oghma's wisdom."~
@10057  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Brandock will keep the book and his notes about its former contents until he returns into his home land Amn, where he will ask for further help in the Temple of Oghma in Amn.~
@10058  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Brandock wants to show his restored book to the priests of Oghma. The Temple of Oghma is in the Dock's District in Athkatla.~
@10059  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Brandock showed his restored book to the priests in the Temple of Oghma is in the Dock's District in Athkatla. They need a King's Tear and 5000 gold to help further with the book.~
@10060  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Brandock wants to return to the Temple of Oghma is in the Dock's District in Athkatla.~
@10061  = ~Brandock Wants to Restore his Book

Brandock visited the Temple of Oghma to gather more knowledge about what to do with the De Simplex Magicae. "Oghma's Wisdom" as mentioned in the note inside the book should be fulfilled then. What happens next will be up to Brandock. I am sure he will tell me when he decided on what to do with the book now.~
@10062  = ~Brandock's Scroll Scribing Skills

Brandock wants us to keep any cursed scrolls we find so we can use the magic in them for something useful.~
@10063  = ~Brandock's Scroll Scribing Skills

Brandock promised to scribe a scroll on our next rest - no matter where.~
@10064  = ~Brandock's Scroll Scribing Skills

Brandock overcame his fear of setting fire to his surroundings when scribing a spell scroll. From now on, he will be able write one scroll per day anywhere.~
@10065  = ~Brandock Changes the Book of Infinite Spells

Brandock offers to reorganize the Book of Infinite Spells so every page I'll open now can be reopened later.
I should scroll though the book until I reach the last page. Upon turning a page, Brandock will tell me when he's finished with whatever he's doing to get them to open later. He also said he will not react to pages that were already opened before in case they appear again.~
@10066  = ~Brandock Changes the Book of Infinite Spells

Brandock finished rewriting the Book of Infinite Spells. Now older pages can be reopened, too.~
@10067  = ~Brandock Changes the Book of Infinite Spells~
